{
  "stem": "3277.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But nothing happened, nothing special, because I could see people without any legs, and terrible, terrible-- And-- and they had problems even to-- to take those people to the hospital, because it was so many, and they didn't have the transportation.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then, what I found out, that that company, the shoe business, was bombed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And the whole crew got killed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "If they had finished my shoes a little bit-- let's say a minute or two minutes later-- I wouldn't have a chance.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I would have-- because, because of that alarm, I would have to stay in that store, and I would get killed.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "This was the first chance that I got alive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I got some more occasions like this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And again, Jewish organizations, you used to feed us and give us some money.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we still start to go farther to the east.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And in the meantime, what happened that the Soviet government made an agreement with the-- with Hitler's government to divide Poland in two.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "The first, the first side, they-- they made an agreement to occupy and the Soviet Union to occupy the east side.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Then, we were already-- and this happened on the 17th of September.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And we were, and then we were among-- you know, from one side, the Germans were coming from the west to east, and the Russian army used to come from east to the west.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And they established the border on the river Bug, B-U-G.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And then, then it was a little bit easier, because it was no bombardments, because we were on the Soviet side.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And I-- and of course, I used to meet people from my town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "I would ask about my brother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And finally, I-- a son of my brother's boss met me.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
